entries.femaleVariant: No. The rest will stay here in camp.
V, you're here.
What is she doing here?
I forbade you from even breathing on that Militech convoy so you call in your friend?
I am starting to wonder.
Uh-huh. That's exactly why I had V come and stand right in front of you. Do you think I'm that stupid?
Got no notion what's going on.
"Forbade" Panam from doing something?
You really think you can "forbid" Panam from doing anything?
Trust me – no point. She'll do whatever she wants.
No, she won't. Not if she plans to stay in this family.
Got no fuckin' clue what's going on here.
Dammit to hell, Saul!
Are you seriously considering letting that Basilisk slip through our fingers?
I am.
Or pissing Militech off so they hammer us into the dirt right here?
Shit, Panam, can you please tell him…?
I've already tried. Let it go, Mitch.
The Biotechnica people will be here in an hour. Try not to cock anything else up before then.
I can't believe it. There he goes, off to paint the grass green.
What's this about a Basilisk?
Bein' unusually quiet.
Bein' unusually quiet. What's up?
I see no point in arguing with Saul. We can't win.
So – givin' up?
Of course not. We'll take the Basilisk ourselves, then wait for Saul to admit we were right.
Either that or to boot us out of the family.
It's an armored Militech cargo panzer – junk from back in 2060 or so.
They want to peddle it off to a backwards country, somewhere it can still pass as a technological wonder.
The Militech convoy will take the one-oh-one, right past us.
Shame not to say hello.
Lemme guess – whole thing's your idea?
How did you know?
Saul wouldn't be quite so pissed if it weren't.
What's the plan?
'Member when you told me to give you a good kick in the pants?
On the contrary, easy as pie. There won't even be much security on the convoy.
Plus, we'll be doing our part towards furthering the cause of world peace.
Thought you and Saul were getting along.
I believe V is right. If this had been Saul's idea, he would've seen it as the greatest plan on God's green earth.
'Member, a while back, told me to give you a solid kick in the pants if I saw you divin' in the stupid pool again?
Why should this beast wind up being used in some little third world skirmish?
Basilisk worth a fight with Saul?
Bull. Saul isn't that petty.
He's simply a coward. He would rather play it safe, bide his time. For the family.
Thought the Biotechnica job was a bust.
Thought the Biotechnica contract had withered and died.
This Basilisk worth another fight with Saul?
I do. Yet that was before our tandem raid on the Raffen camp.
The family is falling apart. If we fall into this Biotechnica rut, no one will ever take us seriously again.
Why's Saul got his briefs in a bunch over this Basilisk?
Saul insists we see it through to the end – to prove the Aldecaldos keep their word.
Crop protection! Who gives a damn about crop protection?!
All Saul is going to prove is that a corp can walk all over us, and we'll say thank you and ask for more.
OK, so you do wanna go behind Saul's back, dragged me here specifically for that.
Cassidy, Ted, Carol and Bob – also on board.
He's afraid Militech will destroy us if we pick a fight with it.
He thinks it safer to stick with the corporations. Like Biotechnica – what a joke!
We would rather go back to plying the trade we know best – logistics.
Meanin' smugglin'.
That's what I said.
I believe you lost your opportunity there.
Nope, different, that – rescue mission. Someone from the family.
Now, you're out to plain trick him.
If you plan to lecture me, you can damn well go right now.
Terrible idea, all this. Sorry, can't, won't get involved.
entries.maleVariant: Terrible idea, all this. Sorry, I can't-- won't get involved.

entries.femaleVariant: Suit yourself.
And you plan to grab the Basilisk how?
But if you change your mind...
Fuck, Mitch. You heard her. She said this is not her concern.
entries.maleVariant: Fuck, Mitch. You heard him. He said this is not his concern.

entries.femaleVariant: Thought you and Saul'd agreed to bury your carbines.
Thanks, V.
So did I. But it seems that's only true when somebody is trying to kill us.
'Zactly. You saved his life. Wanna fuck things up all over again now?
entries.maleVariant: Zactly. You saved his life. You wanna fuck things up all over again now?

entries.femaleVariant: OK, let's go talk to the rest.
I saved his life, yet somehow he still ignores everything I say.
So I do believe we have come full circle.
I want patrols every half hour, reporting directly to me.
Are we preparing for a visit from Biotechnica?
The Raffens could surprise us at any moment.
I don't want any more surprises.
No. OK, everyone listen. Militech will transport the Basilisk in parts distributed across two trucks.
Wait – do I sense a quiver in your voice?
Fuck you.
Haven't said I'd help just yet.
The convoy we'll halt at the railroad crossing on the one-oh-one.
We'll attack from behind, then get the hell out and away.
Questions, comments, motions?
OK, I'm in.
It all seems too perfect, too easy…
Don't wanna get involved.
Panam's got a beef with Saul, I know. But you guys?
OK. I'm in.
Hmm. OK. Thanks.
It's all too... easy. Convenient to arrange.
The exact tech you need. Comin' your way almost served on a silver platter.
Panam's got a beef with Saul, I know. But you guys...?
Nice job, sunshine.
Mhm. Damn short, sweet and pertinent.
None of that sad-sack bullshit Saul likes to tack on.
A few years back, nobody would have given corpo work a second thought.
We want a good name, we just need good gear and good jobs.
And Saul would see that if he pulled his head out of his caboose once in a while.
Yes. Saul also claimed it stinks to high heaven.
Intel on the convoy – where'd you get it?
Carol hacked the Militech comms channel. Is that enough for you?
What's this Basilisk nonsense?
So, just the four vets on board with the plan, nobody else?
We didn't bother asking the others.
There was too great a risk someone would take it to Saul.
Besides, only the vets understand what we stand to gain by having a Basilisk.
To do it all behind my back, is that it?
And you guys'd rather...?
Did you try to get Saul on board again? No luck, huh?
Just the vets on board, nobody else?
Or a Fourth Corporate War?
You're not blowing this a little out of proportion...?
Besides, we'll look good, aware, prepared.
Get the sense this fight's grown stale. C'mon, put some feeling into it.
Feel like this fight's been goin' on a while.
Wow, a lot's changed since I left.
But a chance like this...
A chance at what? Rotting up the job we came here to do?
No. This discussion ended long ago.
Wow, seems a lot changed while I was away.
No, nothing has changed at all.
V?
Lemme guess. Your idea?
Yes! A craft like that would finally put us back on the right path.
Basilisk – what's Saul's problem with it?
Sounds pretty darn risky, this.
Sounds pretty risky to me.
We'll make better use of it right here in America.
First, we'll ride to the station.
The train engine we need to block the convoy's way is there.
Is everything clear?
I think I heard a little shake in that voice.
But – are you sure you didn't leave any tracks? Militech won't notice a thing?
Are you trying to insult me, Bobby?
You did not.
Are we going?
I'm riding with.
Are you riding with us, or will we meet you there?
V?
Well? V?
We'll meet there.
Ridin' with you.
Meet you there.
Excellent. Let's get going.
Not a problem.
Let's go.
[Sit]
Come on, let's go.
Aw, come on. Did your hands get clammy, too?
Screw you.
OK, OK. Forget I even asked.
If you don't want to, you don't need to drop into the middle of this.
But we could use your help – that's undeniable.
[Get in]
OK, I'm in.
[Stand] Don't wanna get involved.
It all seems too perfect, too easy…
[Stand] I'm riding with.
[Stand] We'll meet there.
[Get up]
